== German ==

=== Etymology ===

From [[Latin]] ''cancellarius'', ushers who sat at the lattice work screens (''cancelli'') of a law court; [[Latin]] ''cancelli'', lattice-work placed before a window, doorway, tribunal of a judge or other places.

=== Noun ===

'''Kanzler''' ''m.''

# [[chancellor]]
# ''abbreviation of [[Bundeskanzler]]''

